index 43b734d..0c5f604 100644
--- a/docs/python-api.rst
+++ b/docs/python-api.rst
@@ -663,6 +663,13 @@ If the record does not exist a ``NotFoundError`` will be raised:
     except NotFoundError:
         print("Dog not found")
 
+You can also look up a record using other columns, by passing them as keyword arguments. This is useful for columns with a unique index on them::
+
+    >>> db.table("collections").get(name="entries")
+    {'id': 1, 'name': 'entries', 'model': 'ada'}
+
+Multiple keyword arguments are combined with ``and``. A ``NotFoundError`` is raised if no record matches, and a ``sqlite_utils.db.MultipleResults`` exception is raised if more than one record matches. Passing a column that does not exist raises ``sqlite_utils.db.InvalidColumns``.
+
 .. _python_api_schema:
 
 Showing the schema
